## 🛠️ How to Run

### Prerequisites
- Ubuntu 20.04 + ROS Noetic
- Python 3.8+
- Required packages:
  ```bash
  sudo apt install ros-noetic-rosbag ros-noetic-image-view python3-rosbag
  pip3 install ultralytics opencv-python
Steps
Clone & Build
bash

编辑



cd ~/catkin_ws/src
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/vehicle_detection.git
cd ~/catkin_ws
catkin build
source devel/setup.bash
Place your .bag file
Put the assignment .bag file (e.g., 2026-02-02-17-57-27.bag) in your home directory or specify its full path.
Run the detector
bash

编辑



roslaunch vehicle_detection detector.launch bag_file:=/full/path/to/your/file.bag
Example:
bash

编辑



roslaunch vehicle_detection detector.launch bag_file:=/mnt/c/Users/15363/Desktop/2026-02-02-17-57-27.bag
View results
A window will pop up showing real-time detection with bounding boxes and labels.
🧠 Method Description
Detection Model: YOLOv8n (YOLOv8 nano) from the ultralytics library.
Chosen for its balance of speed and accuracy—critical for onboard drone applications.
Pre-trained on COCO dataset (includes "car", "bus", "truck" classes).
ROS Integration:
Subscribes to /camera/image_raw topic from rosbag.
Publishes annotated images to /vehicle_detection/output.
Uses cv_bridge to convert between ROS Image messages and OpenCV format.
Visualization: Real-time display via OpenCV (cv2.imshow).
Why not other models? Faster R-CNN is too slow; SSD lacks accuracy for small distant vehicles in aerial views. YOLOv8 offers optimal trade-off.
🔍 Reflection & Critical Analysis
(a) What did you learn?
ROS Message Pipeline: I learned how to subscribe to image topics, process data in real time, and publish results—all while managing callbacks and threading in rospy.
Integration of Deep Learning with ROS: I gained hands-on experience embedding a PyTorch-based model (YOLOv8) into a ROS node, handling GPU/CPU inference, and managing frame rates.
(b) How did you use AI tools?
I used AI assistants (like Qwen) to:
Debug WSL/ROS path issues (e.g., /mnt/c/... vs Linux paths).
Generate boilerplate code for extract_images.py and launch files.
Benefits: Accelerated troubleshooting and reduced syntax errors.
Limitations: AI cannot access my local file system, so I had to manually verify paths and topic names. Final logic and integration were done by me.
(c) How to improve accuracy?
Fine-tune YOLOv8 on aerial vehicle datasets (e.g., VisDrone). The default COCO model struggles with top-down vehicle views.
Add temporal smoothing (e.g., Kalman filter) to reduce flickering and stabilize bounding boxes across frames.
(d) Real-world challenges on a drone
Latency & Frame Rate: Onboard GPUs may not sustain real-time inference at high resolution, causing missed detections during fast flight.
Lighting & Weather: Shadows, glare, or rain can degrade image quality, leading to false negatives—something not captured in the provided rosbag.
